“This is a common fear that that AI and Machine Learning will take away jobs from Humans. What are your opinions on this? Discuss”
I have mixed feelings about it
I think it goes both ways... Yeah, it's making some jobs obsolete, but is also creating jobs

Humans are always behind AI and Machine Learning. Humans are needed to program the software, the computers, etc
I think it really should be a good thing for people, but it has the potential to be exploited by a few

Human errors can cause fatal mistakes by just doing one wrong thing. In AI and ML terms, you can keep testing till you reduce error margins and not have one bad mistake that cause an uproar so to speak

So I've gone back and forth on this.

A decade ago with computers people said that accountants would be finished. Cause computers could do math on their own, but instead of making accountants obsolete, people started using computers to tackle more complicated math problems
I think as long as we are able to adapt and keep creating new jobs for people, it's good and can make us as humans a lot smarter, faster, healthier, etc

So, it holds that AI should create new jobs and allow people to transition. However, AI is completely different than other tech revolutions in that it is slowly destroying the barriers between humans and computers
